			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Guide to soloing the luggald broodmother<a name="43955"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jun 3 04 12:38 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span><b></b>So you want to impress your friends and show off your bardly prowess and get some cool loot to boot? Solo the luggald broodmother!  
<br />

<br />
<b>My song lineup:</b>
<br />
1.  Chant #1
<br />
2.  Chant #2
<br />
3.  Chant #3
<br />
4.  Chant #4
<br />
5.  Angstilches Assonance
<br />
6.  Chorus of Maar
<br />
7.  Psalm of Veeshan/Song of higsun (will explain when to use which)
<br />
8.  Kazumi's note of preservation
<br />

<br />
<b>AA -</b> you'll need fading memories or a druid to evac you to lose aggro at one point. I guess you could try just zoning but it's much less elegant.  Run 3 is also a must.
<br />

<br />
<b>Who is the broodmother and how does she work?</b>
<br />
The luggald broodmother is a triggered 3 day spawn.  She is triggerd by killing the luggald ambassador located in the hallway in the Crypt of Nadox. Location is approx +750, +1500. He is very difficult to track even if you're close so just invis up and scout him out. Nothing down there sees invis.
<br />

<br />
Once the ambassador dies, the broodmother spawns immediatly with a few guards. At this point she is untargetable and will remain so for about 15-20 mins.  She will walk around the main hatchery room and more guardians will join her. The guardians are warriors (regular looking luggalds) and clerics (the robed luggalds). 
<br />

<br />
<b>How to kill her</b>
<br />
First, kill the ambassador. This is easy to do. The hallway is large enough you can just dot kite him while you run in a circle. You will get more adds in the hallway but no need to worry.  As soon as the ambassador dies sing invis and then use Fading Memories or have your druid evac you.  We want to do this to lose aggro until the broodmother becomes targetable.
<br />

<br />
Whether you used FM or evac'd, stay invis and go to the mouth of the tunnel at +500, +1200.  The broodmother will eventually walk right in front of that tunnel and it is there that she will become targetable.  It will take longer than you think but be patient.  
<br />

<br />
Once she becomes targetable, hit her with angstilches assonance and then start running for the torgarin zone line.
<br />

<br />
A few things to note here:  1) make sure you are very famiiar with how to get to the torgarin zone. 2) make very very sure you warn the zone you're training the  broodmother and her guardians to the zoneline. 3) On the way to the zoneline you will have to run through a trapdoor. Historiclly, you could just run through this trapdoor as if it were a fake wall or something. Since dx9 i've had trouble getting through and usually employ the help of a friend to open it from the other side as i'm running. (The lever to open the trapdoor is only available on one side and it's not the side you'll be running from.)  While i'm running i try to stay invis so i don't get hit by all the other critters between me and torgarin.  Sometimes the cleric guardians get nuke happy in which case I use Kazumi's and PoV to mitigate that spell damage till i zone out.
<br />

<br />
Now, let's say you've got the broodmother successfully trained to the torgarin line, this is where you zone out into torgarin and wait a minute.  The broodmother will wait around but most of her guardians will leave.  After a few minutes, invis and go back into nadox.  If you're lucky you'll have the broodmother solo.  If any of her cleric guardians are still around use highsun to gate them back to their spawn point.  Now you can use the large area by the torgarin line to chant down the broodmother.
<br />

<br />
She has a lot of HP but does not summon.  She hits for around 400 unmitigated so it's important to stay out of her range which is rather large.  If she has the hammer she'll proc it like crazy and stuns are bad news so be wary of that.  She also will despawn if she has no aggro for a certain amount of time, maybe 10 mins or so. I.e. if you die and want a 2nd chance you'd better haul bard to get back to her in time.
<br />

<br />
<b>Your handsome reward can include:</b>
<br />
<img src="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/equipment/rpics/bone-bladed_battlehammer.jpg">
<br />

<br />
Lavastone Ring (Nadox)  
<br />
LORE ITEM MAGIC ITEM  
<br />
Weight: 0.3 Size: TINY 
<br />
Slot: FINGERS  
<br />
AC: +8 Sta: +12 Wis: +10 Int: +10 Cold Resist: +12 HP: +70 Mana: +55  
<br />
Classes: All Classes  
<br />
Races: All Races  
<br />

<br />
<img src="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/equipment/rpics/spiritmastershroud.jpg">
<br />

<br />
And a pair of craptastic boots that only dissapoints.
<br />

<br />
She only ever has one of these items. If she has the hammer it is visible once she becomes targetable. It looks like an OT gate hammer.
<br />

<br />
The best advice I can give is familiarize yourself with the zone and practice. It took me a few tries to get this down but like all good bard solo jobs it takes some finesse.
<br />

<br />
Good luck and have fun. Oh, and if you try to steal her from me on Xev, i'll claw your eyes out. <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" /> 
<br />

<br />
Kluvan Brightwood
<br />
Xev
<br />

<br />

<br />
</span></td>
